<doc id="261435" wikidata="Q288071" url="?curid=261435" title="Rákoskeresztúr">
<text>Rákoskeresztúr () is a former town in Hungary now part of District XVII of Budapest. Rákoskeresztúr was united with Budapest on January 1, 1950.

==Background==

The first written mark (the name &quot;Pousarakusa&quot;, in modern Hungarian &quot;Pósarákosa&quot;) was a title-deed written in 1265. The name was given by the region&#x27;s first occupant. In that title-deed the region was given to the Crusaders of Upper-Heviz. The village was almost destroyed in the Turkish assault. In 1662, only eight peasant- and 2 cotter families lived in it. From 1727 to 1950, it was counted as a town. In 1880, Rákoshegy and Rákosliget are cut off from Rákoskeresztúr. In 1950, Rákoskeresztúr, Rákoshegy, Rákosliget and the newly built Rákoskert were joined together as the XVII. district of Budapest.</text><links>
<link wikidata="Q288071" start="0" end="14" title="Rákoskeresztúr" label="Rákoskeresztúr"/>
